<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy - Gleania" %>
<% content_for :description, "Learn how Gleania collects, uses, and protects your information." %>

<section class="relative pt-28 pb-10 overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-primary-500/5 to-transparent"></div>
  <div class="absolute -top-24 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[650px] h-[650px] bg-primary-500/10 rounded-full blur-[140px] pointer-events-none"></div>

  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: December 16, 2025</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pb-16">
  <div class="legal-card">
    <div class="article-prose">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how Gleania ("Gleania", "we", "us") collects, uses, and shares information
        when you use our website and application (the "Service"). Gleania is an intelligent interview assistant
        designed to help job seekers organize, track, and optimize their job search process.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      
      <h3>Account Information</h3>
      <p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name and email address</li>
        <li>Password (securely hashed)</li>
        <li>OAuth identifiers if you sign in with Google</li>
        <li>Profile preferences and settings</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Resumes and Career Documents</h3>
      <p>When you upload resumes, we collect and process:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Resume files (PDF, DOCX, etc.)</li>
        <li>Extracted text content from your documents</li>
        <li>Skills, experience, and qualifications identified through AI analysis</li>
        <li>Target job roles and companies you specify</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Job Search Data</h3>
      <p>As you use the Service, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Job listings you save or apply to</li>
        <li>Interview applications, rounds, and feedback you record</li>
        <li>Companies you're tracking</li>
        <li>Notes and timeline events related to your applications</li>
        <li>Fit assessments comparing your skills to job requirements</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Gmail Integration Data</h3>
      <p>If you connect your Gmail account, we access (with your permission):</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email metadata: sender, subject, date, and labels</li>
        <li>Email snippets and body previews to identify interview-related messages</li>
        <li>We only process emails that appear to be job or interview related</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Usage and Technical Data</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Log data: IP address, browser type, pages visited, timestamps</li>
        <li>Device information: operating system, screen resolution</li>
        <li>Feature usage patterns to improve the Service</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use AI and Machine Learning</h2>
      <p>
        Gleania uses artificial intelligence to enhance your job search experience. Here's how:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Resume Analysis:</strong> AI extracts skills, experience, and qualifications from your uploaded resumes to build your profile.</li>
        <li><strong>Job Matching:</strong> We analyze job listings and compare them to your profile to generate fit assessments and recommendations.</li>
        <li><strong>Email Processing:</strong> AI identifies interview-related emails and extracts relevant opportunity information.</li>
        <li><strong>Job Listing Extraction:</strong> When you add job URLs, AI extracts structured information from job postings.</li>
        <li><strong>Interview Assistance:</strong> AI-powered features help you prepare for interviews and analyze feedback.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We use third-party AI providers (such as OpenAI and Anthropic) to process certain data. Data sent to these 
        providers is used solely for processing your requests and is subject to their respective privacy policies.
        We do not use your data to train AI models.
      </p>

      <h2>Google API Services User Data Policy</h2>
      <p>
        Gleania's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
        <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>,
        including the Limited Use requirements. Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>We only request access to data necessary for the Service's features</li>
        <li>We do not use Google user data to serve advertisements</li>
        <li>We do not sell Google user data to third parties</li>
        <li>We do not use Google user data for purposes unrelated to the Service</li>
        <li>You can disconnect your Google account at any time in Settings</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the Service</li>
        <li>Process your resumes and generate skill profiles</li>
        <li>Sync and analyze interview-related emails (if enabled)</li>
        <li>Calculate fit assessments for job opportunities</li>
        <li>Send transactional emails (account verification, password resets)</li>
        <li>Respond to support requests</li>
        <li>Detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and security issues</li>
        <li>Generate aggregated, anonymized insights to improve the Service</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Information Sharing</h2>
      <p>We may share your information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Companies that help us operate the Service (hosting, email delivery, error monitoring, AI processing)</li>
        <li><strong>AI Providers:</strong> OpenAI and Anthropic for AI-powered features (data is processed per their privacy policies)</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law, court order, or to protect our rights</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We do not share your data with third parties for their marketing purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Data encryption in transit (TLS/HTTPS) and at rest</li>
        <li>Secure password hashing using bcrypt</li>
        <li>OAuth 2.0 for third-party authentication</li>
        <li>Regular security audits and updates</li>
        <li>Access controls and audit logging</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Account data is retained while your account is active</li>
        <li>You can delete your account and associated data at any time</li>
        <li>Synced emails can be disconnected, stopping future syncing</li>
        <li>Some data may be retained for legal or security purposes</li>
        <li>Backups are retained for up to 30 days after deletion</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access and download your personal data</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Delete your account and data</li>
        <li>Object to certain processing activities</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent for optional features</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Your data may be processed in countries other than your own. We ensure appropriate safeguards
        are in place for international transfers, including standard contractual clauses where required.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Service is not intended for children under 16. We do not knowingly collect information
        from children. If you believe we have collected data from a child, please contact us.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes
        by posting the new policy and updating the "Last updated" date. Continued use of the Service
        after changes become effective constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us via
        our <%= link_to "contact page", contact_path %>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
